figure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20is%20changing%20how%20work%20gets%20done%20and%20what%20companies%20produce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETop%20economies%20could%20introduce%20quotas%20to%20mandate%20a%20minimum%20level%20of%20human%20involvement%20in%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHuman%20worker%20quotas%20were%20a%20much-discussed%20topic%20at%20a%20major%20HR%20conference%20in%20London%20this%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDiversity%20and%20inclusion%20quotas%20based%20on%20gender%20and%20race%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-policies-delete-trump-disney-general-motors-pepsi-diversity-target-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equietly%20rolled%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202025.%20But%20as%20AI%20reshapes%20work%2C%20HR%20experts%20say%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20quota%20may%20emerge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demographic%20it%20aims%20to%20deliver%20equity%20for%3F%20The%20human%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20HR%20Symposium%20in%20London%20this%20Tuesday%2C%20analysts%20from%20research%20giant%20Gartner%20predicted%20that%20by%202032%2C%20at%20least%2030%25%20of%20the%20world's%20top%20economies%20will%20require%20%26quot%3Bcertified%20human%20quotas%20mandating%20a%20minimum%20level%20of%20human%20involvement%20in%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnia%20Krasniewska%2C%20group%20vice%20president%20of%20Gartner%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20during%20an%20interview%20at%20the%20conference%20that%20the%20global%20research%20firm's%20prediction%20was%20based%20on%20several%20Gartner%20analyses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20would%20be%20to%20ensure%20humans%20continue%20to%20play%20a%20meaningful%20role%20in%20production%2C%20decision-making%2C%20and%20creative%20processes%20even%20as%20AI%20plays%20a%20greater%20role%20in%20businesses'%20workflow%20and%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20kind%20of%20change%20won't%20be%20organizationally%20driven%3B%20it%20will%20be%20legislation%20driven%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Krasniewska.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20these%20rules%20kick%20in%2C%20organizations%20will%20need%20clear%20processes%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-execs-3-things-companies-get-right-using-deploying-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eredeploy%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20way%20to%20prove%20they're%20doing%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20Australia's%20High%20Court%20ruled%20that%20the%20country's%20Fair%20Work%20Commission%20can%20investigate%20whether%20an%20employer%20could%20have%20redeployed%20workers%20by%20restructuring%20work%20before%20declaring%20a%20redundancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20arose%20from%20a%20case%20involving%20a%20business%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshadow-stand-ins-workers-secretly-outsourcing-their-jobs-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoutsourcing%20to%20contractors%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20laying%20off%20employees%2C%20but%20it%20will%20also%20impact%20companies'%20decisions%20about%20the%20redeployment%20of%20the%20human%20workforce%20alongside%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20to%20see%20more%20legislation%20like%20this%20to%20be%20announced%20in%20the%20coming%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Krasniewska%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20work%20is%20produced%20by%20AI%2C%20business%20leaders%20will%20also%20need%20to%20consider%20how%20to%20handle%20accountability%20for%20errors%20that%20AI-produced%20work%20may%20create.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrasniewska%20pointed%20to%20the%20example%20of%20medical%20imaging%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20AI%20read%20it%2C%20you%20pursued%20a%20course%20of%20treatment%2C%20and%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20the%20reading%20was%20wrong%2C%20who%20takes%20accountability%20for%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20popular%20fix%20is%20to%20keep%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flattice-ai-agents-humans-work-jobs-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehuman%20in%20the%20loop%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20The%20EU's%20AI%20Act%2C%20for%20example%2C%20requires%20a%20%26quot%3Bmeaningful%26quot%3B%20level%20of%20human%20oversight%20for%20high-risk%20AI%20systems%2C%20ensuring%20that%20people%20can%20step%20in%20to%20correct%20AI%20outputs%20that%20endanger%20health%2C%20safety%2C%20or%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20foolproof%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20Deloitte%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20consulting%20and%20accounting%20firms%2C%20agreed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeloitte-australia-issues-refund-ai-assurance-project-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epartially%20refund%20the%20Australian%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20it%20produced%20a%20report%20with%20errors%2C%20including%20academic%20references%20to%20people%20who%20didn't%20exist%20and%20a%20made-up%20quote%20from%20a%20Federal%20Court%20judgment.%20The%20Big%20Four%20firm%20said%20it%20used%20AI%20to%20help%20write%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrasniewska%20said%20businesses%20need%20to%20consider%20how%20to%20track%20where%20the%20human%20interaction%20components%20are%20and%20use%20citations%20and%20watermarks%20on%20information%20so%20that%20it%20is%20clear%20whether%20it%20had%20an%20AI%20component%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20likely%20be%20legislation%20or%20public%20pressure%20around%20the%20need%20to%20have%20some%20form%20of%20disclosure%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOrganizations%20haven't%20necessarily%20thought%20that%20far%20ahead%20as%20to%20what%20we%20should%20do.%20But%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20very%20human%20reality%20of%20sensing%20that%20we%20will%20need%20to%20disclose%20how%20we%20got%20from%20point%20A%20to%20point%20B%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Krasniewska.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgartner-hr-experts-ai-changing-workplace-quotas-mandate-human-involvement-2025-