ssure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20part%20of%20the%20process%20that%20surprised%20me%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-ai-mckinsey-bcg-deloitte-pwc-kpmg-chatbots-ai-tools-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBCG's%20AI%20chatbot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Casey.%20Half%20of%20your%20first%20round%20is%20with%20a%20live%20interviewer%2C%20and%20the%20other%20half%20is%20with%20this%20chatbot.%20You%20basically%20run%20a%20case%20with%20it.%20It%20wasn't%20my%20favorite%20experience.%20You%20don't%20get%20feedback.%20You%20just%20get%20a%20ton%20of%20numbers.%20It's%20not%20like%20a%20real%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20advice%20to%20candidates%20is%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-6-figure-consulting-job-accenture-exxonmobil-career-coach-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvest%20in%20a%20coach%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Coaching%20changed%20everything%20for%20me.%20You%20don't%20need%20to%20run%20a%20hundred%20cases.%20You%20need%20to%20run%20quality%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnsure%20you%20find%20advocates%20within%20the%20firm%20you%20want%20to%20work%20at.%20I%20only%20spoke%20with%20a%20handful%20of%20BYU%20alums%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20five%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20built%20strong%20relationships%20with%20them%2C%20and%20they%20advocated%20for%20me%20during%20the%20recruiting%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20now%20double-majoring%20in%20economics.%20I%20declared%20it%20at%20the%20end%20of%20my%20sophomore%20year%20to%20get%20more%20familiar%20with%20business%20topics%20before%20starting%20my%20internship%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20help%20me%20land%20the%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuccess%20is%20often%20defined%20as%20being%20the%20best%20among%20people%20who%20are%20all%20doing%20the%20same%20thing.%20But%20I%20think%20I%20got%20the%20offer%20not%20because%20I%20was%20the%20best%2C%20but%20because%20I%20was%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F